==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|differen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|differer|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|differō||carry apart, put off, defer; differ}}, from {{term|dis-||apart|lang=la}} + {{m|la|ferō||carry, bear}}. Compare Ancient Greek {{term|διαφέρω|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-differ.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈdɪfə/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪfə(r)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# Not to have the same [[traits]], [[characteristic|characteristics]].
# {{context|people, groups, etc.|lang=en}} To have [[diverge|diverging]] [[opinion]]s, [[disagree]].
#* Canning
#*: If the honourable gentleman '''differs''' with me on that subject, I differ as heartily with him, and shall always rejoice to differ.

